---

**What the last 48 hours tell me:**

Monday's 7.18km was exactly right — 7:13/km, avg HR 126, never forced it past 143 max. That's the discipline this base phase demands. You didn't hero it, you executed it. Respect.

Saturday's 11.65km long run was solid too — 8:08/km, HR 128, aerobic training effect 2.8. Your body is responding.

July mileage: **31.7km through July 6.** You need ~100km this month. That's ~68km across the remaining ~25 days. Completely doable if you hit your scheduled runs — but there's no room to skip sessions.

---

